      • getValidationSet

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> getValidationSet()
        Description copied from interface: GameTreeInterface
        This method returns an ordered list of Integers. In this list each position represents the number of different possible moves for each depth of the game. Position 0 represents the number of moves possible from the root of the tree and so forth. There is no integer in this list for terminal nodes.
        Specified by:
        getValidationSet in interface GameTreeInterface
        Returns:
        ordered List of Integer.
